(2). Get all employees with salary greater than 50,000.
(3). Fetch employee names sorted by joining date.
(4). Get the top 5 highest-paid employees.
(5). How many employees are in the company?
(6). Get department-wise employee count.
(7). Find all employees whose names start with 'A'.
(8). Fetch employees from departments 1, 3, and 5.
(9). Get employees who joined between 2020 and 2022.
(10) Find employees who don’t have a manager assigned.


